'''''Sagra buqueti''''', common name '''Frog-legged Leaf Beetle''',  is a species of [[beetle]]s belonging to the family [[Chrysomelidae]].

==Description==
''Sagra buqueti'' can reach a length of {{convert|25|-|50|mm}}. These iridescent colorful beetles have a striking sexual dimorphism. The males are very larger and have very long and strong hind-legs (hence the common name). The basic colour is metallic green, with reddish and golden reflections on the elytra. Cocoons of this species can be found in the jungle on climbing vines.

==Distribution==
This species can be found in [[Thailand]] and in [[Malaysia]].

